## 🚀 Feature Proposal

When creating a [table](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs#tables) in a sheet, it would be nice to able to set the `width` of a column directly through the column definition.

## Motivation

Creating a table and then setting the width of the columns is currently a 2-step-process. This is cumbersome and makes the code harder to read.

## Example

Consider this code, compatible with the current state of the library:
```ts
    const sheetOrganizations = workbook.addWorksheet("Organizations");
    sheetOrganizations.addTable({
      name: "Organizations",
      ref: "A1",
      headerRow: true,
      style: {
        showRowStripes: true,
      },
      columns: [
        { name: "ID", filterButton: true },
        { name: "Name", filterButton: true },
        { name: "Date created", filterButton: true },
        { name: "Credits", filterButton: true },
        { name: "License", filterButton: true },
        { name: "Valid from", filterButton: true },
        { name: "Valid until", filterButton: true },
      ],
      rows: rowsOrganizations,
    });
    sheetOrganizations.columns[0].width = 40;
    sheetOrganizations.columns[1].width = 40;
    sheetOrganizations.columns[2].width = 13;
    sheetOrganizations.columns[3].width = 10;
    sheetOrganizations.columns[4].width = 10;
    sheetOrganizations.columns[5].width = 13;
    sheetOrganizations.columns[6].width = 13;
```

It becomes very hard to correlate a specific colum to the width. It would be much more convenient to have everything in a single place.

```ts
    const sheetOrganizations = workbook.addWorksheet("Organizations");
    sheetOrganizations.addTable({
      name: "Organizations",
      ref: "A1",
      headerRow: true,
      style: {
        showRowStripes: true,
      },
      columns: [
        { name: "ID", filterButton: true, width: 40 },
        { name: "Name", filterButton: true, width: 40 },
        { name: "Date created", filterButton: true, width: 13 },
        { name: "Credits", filterButton: true, width: 10 },
        { name: "License", filterButton: true, width: 10 },
        { name: "Valid from", filterButton: true, width: 13 },
        { name: "Valid until", filterButton: true, width: 13 },
      ],
      rows: rowsOrganizations,
    });
```

comments.body:
@Siemienik From what I see from the `TableColumnProperties` type, there is no `width` property. Why has this issue been closed?

```ts
export interface TableColumnProperties {
	/**
	  * The name of the column, also used in the header
	  */
	name: string;
	/**
	  * Switches the filter control in the header
	  * @default false
	  */
	filterButton?: boolean;
	/**
	  * Label to describe the totals row (first column)
	  * @default 'Total'
	  */
	totalsRowLabel?: string;
	/**
	  * Name of the totals function
	  * @default 'none'
	  */
	totalsRowFunction?: 'none' | 'average' | 'countNums' | 'count' | 'max' | 'min' | 'stdDev' | 'var' | 'sum' | 'custom';
	/**
	  * Optional formula for custom functions
	  */
	totalsRowFormula?: string;
}
```

By the way, it would be nice if table cells benefited from the `style` property
